---
import SupportPage from '../../components/SupportPage.astro';
---
<SupportPage
  locale="en"
  path="/support/faq.html"
  title="FAQ | GYUTRON Support"
  description="Frequently asked questions about GYUTRON industrial hardware — products and compatibility, samples and quotations, shipping and lead time, warranty and after-sales, and documentation and integration for B2B customers and system integrators."
  eyebrow="Help & Support"
  heading="Frequently Asked Questions"
  crumb="FAQ"
  intro="Answers to the questions we hear most often from manufacturers, system integrators and B2B buyers — grouped by topic."
  heroImage="/product-vision-cell.png"
>
  <h2>Products &amp; Compatibility</h2>
  <div class="support-faq">
    <details>
      <summary>What products does GYUTRON provide?</summary>
      <p>GYUTRON supplies industrial intelligent hardware: machine-vision and code-reading cameras, smart vision sensors, proximity and environmental sensors, rugged Android PDAs and RFID handhelds, barcode scanners, dimensional gauges and measurement instruments, plus related automation components — for manufacturers and system integrators worldwide.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can GYUTRON help match products to my application?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Share your application, operating environment, target throughput and interface requirements with our sales-engineering team and we will recommend a suitable configuration rather than just a part number.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you support OEM or ODM projects?</summary>
      <p>Yes. For qualified volume programs we support custom configurations, firmware, housings, connectors and private labeling. Share your specification and target quantity to scope a solution.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Are your products suitable for industrial environments?</summary>
      <p>Our hardware is designed for industrial use, with IP-rated housings on applicable models and ratings stated per product. Confirm the specific environmental and ingress rating for your conditions on the product datasheet or with our team.</p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <h2>Samples &amp; Quotation</h2>
  <div class="support-faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Can I request samples or evaluation units?</summary>
      <p>Evaluation units are available for qualified projects. Tell us about your application, interface and expected volume through <a href="/contact-sales.html">Contact Sales</a> and we will advise on availability.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do I request a quotation?</summary>
      <p>Send the product model(s), quantity and target date through <a href="/contact-sales.html">Contact Sales</a> and our team will prepare a quotation.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What information should I provide for a quote?</summary>
      <p>Product model or application description, quantity, required interface/configuration, target delivery date and destination country/region. The more detail you provide, the more accurate the quotation.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Is there a minimum order quantity?</summary>
      <p>Minimums depend on the product line and configuration and are confirmed in the applicable quotation. We work with both pilot/evaluation volumes and series production.</p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <h2>Shipping &amp; Lead Time</h2>
  <div class="support-faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Do you ship internationally?</summary>
      <p>Yes — we ship worldwide. Shipments are arranged from Hong Kong, Shenzhen or supplier warehouses depending on product availability and project requirements. See <a href="/support/shipping-delivery.html">Shipping &amp; Delivery</a>.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What is the typical lead time?</summary>
      <p>In-stock items are dispatched promptly; configured or made-to-order items depend on options and quantity. Confirmed lead times are provided with each quotation.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Which Incoterms do you support?</summary>
      <p>International shipments are arranged under agreed Incoterms such as EXW, FOB or DAP, confirmed on the order. For larger orders we can coordinate with your nominated freight forwarder.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can you arrange partial shipments?</summary>
      <p>Yes. For multi-line orders we can ship available items first rather than holding the entire order for one line, as agreed on the order.</p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <h2>Warranty &amp; After-sales</h2>
  <div class="support-faq">
    <details>
      <summary>What warranty does GYUTRON provide?</summary>
      <p>GYUTRON hardware carries a limited warranty against defects in materials and workmanship. Coverage may vary by product category and project agreement; the applicable terms are confirmed in your quotation, order confirmation or written agreement. See the <a href="/support/warranty.html">Warranty</a> page.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What is not covered under warranty?</summary>
      <p>Typical exclusions include misuse, improper installation, operation outside published specifications, unauthorized modification or repair, accidental or liquid damage beyond the rated protection, and consumable or wear parts. See the <a href="/support/warranty.html">Warranty</a> page for details.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do I request after-sales support?</summary>
      <p>Start by <a href="/support.html">contacting support</a> with the product model, serial number and a description of the issue. Eligible cases are handled through our RMA process.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do you provide repair or replacement service?</summary>
      <p>Yes. In-warranty defects are repaired or replaced at GYUTRON's discretion; paid repair and service are available for out-of-warranty units.</p>
    </details>
  </div>

  <h2>Documentation &amp; Integration</h2>
  <div class="support-faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Can you provide datasheets and technical documents?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Datasheets, manuals and technical documentation are available from your sales engineer or <a href="mailto:info@gyutron.com">info@gyutron.com</a>. A self-service Downloads area is being expanded.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do your products support SDKs or integration guides?</summary>
      <p>Yes. We provide the SDKs, drivers and integration guidance required to bring a device into your platform, line or host application.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can GYUTRON support system integrators?</summary>
      <p>Yes. We work with system integrators and machine builders and can support specification, sample evaluation and integration for project-based deployments.</p>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Can you help evaluate a machine-vision or automation project?</summary>
      <p>Yes. Our application engineers can help assess feasibility, recommend hardware and define an integration approach for vision-inspection, identification and automation projects.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</SupportPage>
